A070001.name: Palindromic integers > 0, whose 'Reverse and Add!' trajectory (presumably) does not lead to another palindrome.

A070002.name: Numbers k such that phi(P(k)) - P(phi(k)) = 1, where P(k) is the largest prime factor of k.

A070003.name: Numbers divisible by the square of their largest prime factor.
formula: Erdős proved that there are x * exp(-(1 + o(1))sqrt(log x log log x)) members of this sequence up to x. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Mar 26 2012

A070004.name: Numbers of the form 5*2^n or 5*3*2^n; a(n) = 5*A029744(n).
formula: a(n) = 5*A029744(n); numbers of the forms 5*2^n and 15*2^n.

A070005.name: Arithmetic mean of prime factors of n is an integer and n is neither a prime nor power of a prime.

A070006.name: Composite numbers that are not a prime power and whose distinct prime divisors' arithmetic mean is a prime.

A070007.name: Arithmetic mean of distinct primes dividing n is a square number.

A070008.name: Arithmetic mean of distinct primes dividing n is a power of 2 (powers of 2 are not left out).

A070009.name: Least number m such that the arithmetic mean of the distinct prime divisors of m is equal to 2^n.

A070010.name: GCD of consecutive values of sum-of-proper divisors.

A070011.name: Numbers n such that number of prime factors divided by the number of distinct prime factors is not an integer.
formula: A001222(n)/A001221(n) (i.e. bigomega(n)/omega(n)) is not an integer.

A070012.name: Floor of number of prime factors of n divided by the number of n's distinct prime factors.

A070013.name: Number of prime factors of n divided by the number of n's distinct prime factors (rounded).

A070014.name: Ceiling of number of prime factors of n divided by the number of n's distinct prime factors.

A070015.name: Least m such that the sum of the aliquot parts of m (A001065) equals n, or 0 if no such number exists.
formula: a(n) = min(x, A001065(x)=n) or a(n)=0 if n is an untouchable number (i.e., if from A005114).

A070016.name: Least m such that Chowla's function value of m [A048050(m)] equals n or 0 if no such number exists.
formula: a(n)=Min{x; A048050(x)=n} or a(n)=0 if n is from A048995.

A070017.name: Least numbers m such that GCD of two consecutive values of cototients, i.e., gcd(cototient(m+1), cototient(m)) equals 2n - 1.

A070018.name: a(n) = smallest prime p = prime(k) such that gcd( prime(k+1) - prime(k), prime(k+2) - prime(k+1) ) = 2n.

A070020.name: At these values of n the first, 2nd and 3rd cyclotomic polynomials all give prime numbers.
formula: n-1, n+1 and 1+n+n^2 are all primes.

A070021.name: 1/n has period 1 in base 10 (but not terminating).
formula: Numbers of the form a*b*c where a is in {3, 9}, b is a power of 2 and c is a power of 5.

A070022.name: 1/n has period 2 in base 10.
formula: a(n) =11*A070023(n). Numbers of the form a*b*c where a is in {11, 33, 99}, b is a power of 2 and c is a power of 5.

A070023.name: 1/n has period 1 in base 10 (including terminating decimals).
formula: a(n) =A070022(n)/11. Numbers of the form a*b*c where a is in {1, 3, 9}, b is a power of 2 and c is a power of 5.

A070024.name: First prime > 10^n in which every substring of length n is prime.

A070025.name: At these values of n, the 1st, 2nd, 3rd and 4th cyclotomic polynomials all give prime numbers.
formula: n-1, n+1, 1+n+n^2 and 1+n^2 are all primes.

A070026.name: Initial, all intermediate and final iterated sums of digits of n are primes.

A070027.name: Prime numbers whose initial, all intermediate and final iterated sums of digits are primes.

A070028.name: Absolute primes: primes whose initial, all intermediate and final sums of digits are primes.

A070029.name: Primes with only prime digits and whose initial, all intermediate and final iterated sums of digits are primes.

A070030.name: Number of closed Knight's tours on a 3 X 2n board.

A070031.name: Expansion of (1+x*C)*C^3, where C = (1-sqrt(1-4*x))/(2*x) is g.f. for Catalan numbers, A000108.
formula: a(n) = leftmost term of M^n*V, M = an infinite tridiagonal matrix with all 1's in the super and subdiagonals and  all 2's in the main diagonal; with the rest zeros. V = Vector [1,2,0,0,0,...]. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Jun 16 2011
D-finite with recurrence: 2*(n+3)*a(n) +(-11*n-15)*a(n-1) +6*(2*n-1)*a(n-2)=0. - _R. J. Mathar_, Aug 25 2013

A070033.name: Least number m such that integer part of sigma(m)/phi(m) equals n.

A070034.name: Numbers n such that n! reduced modulo 2^n is also a power of 2.
formula: Mod[a(n)!, 2^a(n)] = A068496(n) = 2^w for some integer w.

A070035.name: Exponents of 2 when A068496(n) is also a power of 2.

A070037.name: Nonprime numbers k such that sigma(k) == k+1 (mod phi(k)).

A070038.name: a(n) = sum of divisors of n that are at least sqrt(n).

A070039.name: Sum of divisors of n that are smaller than sqrt(n).

A070041.name: Permutation of natural numbers induced by the automorphism df->bf (from the depth-first to breadth-first encoding) acting on the rooted planar binary trees encoded by A014486. (with one-based indexing).

A070042.name: At these values of n the first, 2nd, 3rd, 4th and 5th cyclotomic polynomials all give prime numbers.
formula: C1(n)=n-1, C2(n)=n+1, C3(n)=1+n+n^2, C4(n)=1+n^2 and C5(n)=1+n+n^2+n^3+n^4 are all primes.

A070043.name: Numbers of the form 6*j*k+j+k for positive integers j and k.

A070044.name: Numbers k such that ceiling(k^1.5) is prime.

A070045.name: Primes of the form ceiling(k^1.5) for some integer k.

A070046.name: Number of primes between prime(n) and 2*prime(n) exclusive.
formula: a(n) = primepi(2*prime(n))-n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Aug 28 2014

A070047.name: Number of partitions of n in which no part appears more than twice and no two parts differ by 1.
formula: Expansion of phi(-x^3) / f(-x) in powers of x where phi(), f() are Ramanujan theta functions. - _Michael Somos_, Jun 02 2011
Expansion of q^(1/24) * eta(q^3)^2 / (eta(q) * eta(q^6)) in powers of q. - _Michael Somos_, Dec 04 2002
Euler transform of period 6 sequence [ 1, 1, -1, 1, 1, 0, ...]. - _Michael Somos_, Dec 04 2002
G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (1152 t)) = (2/3)^(1/2) g(t) where q = exp(2 Pi i t) and g is the g.f. of A233006.

A070048.name: Number of partitions of n into odd parts in which no part appears more than thrice.
formula: Expansion of chi(x) * chi(x^2) = psi(x) / psi(-x^2) = phi(-x^4) / psi(-x) = chi(-x^4) / chi(-x) in powers of x where phi(), psi(), chi() are Ramanujan theta functions. - _Michael Somos_, Jul 01 2014
Expansion of q^(1/8) * eta(q^2) * eta(q^4) / (eta(q) * eta(q^8)) in powers of q.
Given g.f. A(x), then B(q) = A(q^8) / q satisifes 0 = f(B(q), B(q^3)) where f(u, v) = (u - v^3) * (u^3 - v) + 3*u*v. - _Michael Somos_, Jul 01 2014
a(n) ~ exp(sqrt(n)*Pi/2) / (4*n^(3/4)) * (1 - (3/(4*Pi) + Pi/32) / sqrt(n)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 31 2015, extended Jan 21 2017

A070050.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 2 rows. In the formula below, P = 2.
formula: T(p, n, i) = Sum_{j=i..n, k=1..i} T(p-1, j, k).

A070051.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 3 rows. In the formula below, P=3.
formula: a(N) = a(3, N), where a(P, N) is defined recursively in A070050.

A070052.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 4 rows.
formula: a(N) = a(4, N), where a(P, N) is defined recursively in A070050.

A070053.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 5 rows.
formula: a(N) = a(5, N), where a(P, N) is defined recursively in A070050.

A070054.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 6 rows.
formula: a(N) = a(6, N), where a(P, N) is defined recursively in A070050.

A070055.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 7 rows.
formula: a(N) = a(7, N), where a(P, N) is defined recursively in A070050.

A070056.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 8 rows.
formula: a(N) = a(8, N), where a(P, N) is defined recursively in A070050.

A070057.name: Number of Bottleneck-Monge matrices with 9 rows.
formula: a(N) = a(9, N), where a(P, N) is defined recursively in A070050.

A070058.name: Decimal expansion of Newton's gravitational constant in SI units.

A070059.name: Decimal expansion of proton mass (in kilograms).

A070060.name: Historical estimate for the mass of an electron (in kg). Incorrect version of A081801.

A070062.name: Decimal expansion of old estimate for Avogadro's constant (in mol^(-1)).

A070063.name: Decimal expansion of the Boltzmann constant k in the 2019 SI system in units J/K.

A070064.name: Decimal expansion of the molar gas constant R according to the 2019 SI system in units J mol^-1 K^-1.

A070065.name: Values of x in positive integer solutions of x^2 + y^5 = z^3, listed in increasing order of z. (If a z-value occurs twice, list solutions in increasing order of y.)

A070066.name: Values of y in positive integer solutions of x^2 + y^5 = z^3, listed in increasing order of z. (If a z-value occurs twice, list solutions in increasing order of y.)

A070067.name: Values of z in positive integer solutions of x^2 + y^5 = z^3, listed in increasing order of z.

A070069.name: a(1) = 11; a(n) = smallest palindromic multiple of a(n-1).

A070070.name: Rounded value of n*L_n(-1) where L is the Laguerre polynomial.
formula: a(n) = round(n * [x^n] exp(x/(1 - x))/(1 - x)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Jun 05 2018

A070071.name: a(n) = n*B(n), where B(n) are the Bell numbers, A000110.
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} n*binomial(n-1, k-1)*Bell(n-k), n >= 2. - _Zerinvary Lajos_, Nov 22 2006
a(n) ~ n^(n+1) * exp(n/LambertW(n)-1-n) / (sqrt(1+LambertW(n)) * LambertW(n)^n). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Mar 13 2014
a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} k * A175757(n,k). - _Alois P. Heinz_, Mar 03 2020

A070072.name: Number of distinct rectangles with integer sides <=n and squarefree area.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{i=1..n} Sum_{j= 1..i} mu(i*j)^2, where mu is the Moebius function (A008683). - _Ridouane Oudra_, Oct 17 2019

A070073.name: Number of distinct cuboids with integer sides <=n and cubefree volume.

A070074.name: a(n)= 2F2(n+1, n+2; 1, 2; 1) *n! *(n+1)! /exp(1), where 2F2 is the generalized hypergeometric function.
formula: a(n) is the n-th power moment of a positive function on a positive half-axis: a(n)=int(x^n*2*hypergeom([], [1, 2], x)*x^(1/2)*BesselK(1, 2*sqrt(x))/exp(1), x=0..infinity), n=0, 1...

A070075.name: Stirling transform of A021009.
formula: In Maple notation, a(0)=1, a(n)= sum(stirling2(n, k)*k!*LaguerreL(k, -1), k=1..n), n=1, 2... . E.g.f.: exp((exp(x)-1)/(2-exp(x)))/(2-exp(x))

A070076.name: Number of n-digit twin prime pairs.
formula: a(n) = A007508(n) - A007508(n-1) [From Max Alekseyev, Jun 16 2011]

A070077.name: Greatest common divisor of n-th squarefree number and n-th cubefree number.

A070078.name: If n is squarefree then Min{k | A070077(k) = n} else 0.

A070079.name: a(n) gives the odd leg of the unique primitive Pythagorean triangle with hypotenuse A002144(n).
formula: a(n) is the odd positive integer with A080109(n) = A002144(n)^2 = a(n)^2 + (4*A070151(n))^2, in this unique decomposition into positive squares (up to order). See the _Lekraj Beedassy_, comment. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Jan 13 2015

A070080.name: Smallest side of integer triangles [a(n) <= A070081(n) <= A070082(n)], sorted by perimeter, lexicographically ordered.

A070081.name: Middle side of integer triangles [A070080(n) <= a(n) <= A070082(n)], sorted by perimeter, sides lexicographically ordered.

A070082.name: Largest side of integer triangles [A070080(n) <= A070081(n) <= a(n)], sorted by perimeter, sides lexicographically ordered.

A070083.name: Perimeters of integer triangles, sorted by perimeter, sides lexicographically ordered.

A070084.name: Greatest common divisor of sides of integer triangles [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)], sorted by perimeter, sides lexicographically ordered.

A070086.name: Areas of integer triangles [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)], rounded values.

A070087.name: P(n) > P(n+1) where P(n) (A006530) is the largest prime factor of n.

A070088.name: Number of integer-sided triangles with perimeter n and prime sides.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/3)} Sum_{i=k..floor((n-k)/2)} sign(floor((i+k)/(n-i-k+1))) * A010051(i) * A010051(k) * A010051(n-i-k). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 13 2019

A070089.name: P(n) < P(n+1) where P(n) (A006530) is the largest prime factor of n.

A070090.name: Number of scalene integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor((n-1)/3)} Sum_{i=k+1..floor((n-k-1)/2)} sign(floor((i+k)/(n-i-k+1))) * A010051(i)_* A010051(k) * A010051(n-i-k). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 13 2019

A070091.name: Number of isosceles integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths.

A070092.name: Number of isosceles integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/3)} Sum_{i=k..floor((n-k)/2)} sign(floor((i+k)/(n-i-k+1))) * ([i = k] + [i = n-i-k] - [k = n-i-k]) * A010051(i) * A010051(k) * A010051(n-i-k), where [] is the Iverson bracket. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 14 2019

A070093.name: Number of acute integer triangles with perimeter n.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/3)} Sum_{i=k..floor((n-k)/2)} (1-sign(floor((n-i-k)^2/(i^2+k^2)))) * sign(floor((i+k)/(n-i-k+1))). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 12 2019

A070094.name: Number of acute integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths.

A070095.name: Number of acute integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/3)} Sum_{i=k..floor((n-k)/2)} (1 - sign(floor((n-i-k)^2/(i^2+k^2)))) * sign(floor((i+k)/(n-i-k+1))) * A010051(i) * A010051(k) * A010051(n-i-k). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 13 2019

A070096.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths which are both acute and scalene.

A070097.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths which are both acute and scalene.

A070098.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n which are acute and isosceles.
formula: a(n) = floor(n/2) - floor(n/(2 + sqrt(2))) - ((n + 1) mod 2). - _David Pasino_, Jun 27 2016

A070099.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths which are acute and isosceles.

A070100.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths which are acute and isosceles.

A070101.name: Number of obtuse integer triangles with perimeter n.

A070102.name: Number of obtuse integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths.

A070103.name: Number of obtuse integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..floor(n/3)} Sum_{i=k..floor((n-k)/2)} (1 - sign(floor((i^2 + k^2)/(n-i-k)^2))) * sign(floor((i + k)/(n-i-k+1))) * A010051(i) * A010051(k) * A010051(n-i-k). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, May 13 2019

A070104.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths which are obtuse and scalene.

A070105.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths which are obtuse and scalene.

A070106.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n which are obtuse and isosceles.

A070107.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths which are obtuse and isosceles.

A070108.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n and prime side lengths which are obtuse and isosceles.

A070109.name: Number of right integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths.
formula: a(n) = A078926(n/2) if n is even; a(n)=0 if n is odd.

A070110.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070111.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an integer triangle with prime sides.

A070112.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is a scalene integer triangle.

A070113.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is a scalene integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070114.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is a scalene integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070115.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an isosceles integer triangle.

A070116.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an isosceles integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070117.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an isosceles integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070118.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute integer triangle.

A070119.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070120.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070121.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute scalene integer triangle.

A070122.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute scalene integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070123.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute scalene integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070124.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute isosceles integer triangle.

A070125.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute isosceles integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070126.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute isosceles integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070127.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse integer triangle.

A070128.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070129.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070130.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse scalene integer triangle.

A070131.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse scalene integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070132.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse scalene integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070133.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse isosceles integer triangle.

A070134.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse isosceles integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070135.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse isosceles integer triangle with prime side lengths.

A070136.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is a right integer triangle.

A070137.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is a right integer triangle with relatively prime side lengths.

A070138.name: Number of integer triangles with an integer area having relatively prime sides a, b and c such that a + b + c = n.

A070139.name: Number of isosceles integer triangles with perimeter n having integral area.

A070140.name: Number of acute integer triangles with perimeter n having integral area.

A070141.name: Number of obtuse integer triangles with perimeter n having integral area.

A070142.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an integer triangle with integer area.

A070143.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an integer triangle with integer area, having relatively prime side lengths.

A070144.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is a scalene integer triangle with integer area.

A070145.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an isosceles integer triangle with integer area.

A070146.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an acute integer triangle with integer area.

A070147.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an obtuse integer triangle with integer area.

A070148.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an integer Heronian triangle having triangular area.

A070149.name: Areas of integer Heronian triangles [A070080(A070142(n)), A070081(A070142(n)), A070082(A070142(n))].

A070150.name: Triangular areas of integer Heronian triangles.

A070151.name: a(n) is one fourth of the even leg of the unique primitive Pythagorean triangle with hypotenuse A002144(n).
formula: 4*a(n) is the even positive integer with A080109(n) = A002144(n)^2 = A070079(n)^2 + (4*a(n))^2 in this unique decomposition (up to order). See A080109 for references. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Jan 13 2015

A070152.name: Take pairs (a,b) with Sum(j = a to b; j) = concatenation of a and b. Sort pairs on b then a. This sequence gives a of each pair.

A070153.name: Take pairs (a,b) with Sum(j = a to b; j) = concatenation of a and b. Sort pairs on b then a. This sequence gives b of each pair.

A070154.name: Number of terms in the simple continued fraction expansion of Sum(k=0,n,(-1)^k/(2k+1)), the Leibniz-Gregory series for Pi.

A070155.name: Numbers n such that n-1, n+1 and 1+n^2 are prime numbers.
formula: For n>1, a(n)^2 = A242720(pi(a(n)-2)) - 2, where pi(n) is the prime counting function (A000720). - _Vladimir Shevelev_, Sep 02 2014

A070156.name: n-1,n+1,1+n^2 and 1+n^4 are all prime numbers.

A070157.name: n-1, n+1, 1+n^2, 1+n^4 and 1+n^8 are all prime numbers.

A070159.name: Numbers k such that phi(k)/(sigma(k)-k) is an integer.
formula: { a(k) } = { n in N | A000010(n)/A001065(n) is an integer }.

A070160.name: Nonprime numbers n such that q = phi(n)/(sigma(n) - n - 1) is an integer.

A070161.name: Nonprime numbers n such that q=phi(n)/(sigma(n)-n-1) is an integer and n is not a prime square.
formula: q=A000010(n)/A048050(n) and n is not in A001248.

A070162.name: Numbers k such that k - phi(k) - 1 is a prime.

A070165.name: Irregular triangle read by rows giving trajectory of n in Collatz problem.
formula: T(n,k) = T^{(k)}(n) with the k-th iterate of the Collatz map T with T(n) = 3*n+1 if n is odd and T(n) = n/2 if n is even, n >= 1. T^{(0)}(n) = n. k = 0, 1, ..., A008908(n) - 1. - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Mar 20 2014

A070166.name: Irregular triangle read by rows giving T(n,k) = number of rooted graphs on n + 1 nodes with k edges (n >= 0, 0 <= k <= n(n-1)/2).

A070167.name: a(n) is the smallest starting value that produces a Collatz sequence in which n occurs.

A070168.name: Irregular triangle of Terras-modified Collatz problem.
formula: See Lagarias, pp. 4-7, eqs. (2.1), (2.4) with (2.5) and (2.6).
T(n,k) = T^{(k)}(n), with the iterations of the Terras-modified Collatz map: T(n) = n/2 if n is even and otherwise (3*n+1)/2, n >= 1. T^{(0)}(n) = n.

T(n,k) = lambda(n,k)*n + rho(n,k), with lambda(n,k) = (3^X(n,k,-1))/2^k and rho(n,k) = sum(x(n,j)*(3^X(n,k,j))/ 2^(k-j), j=0..(k-1)) with X(n,k,j) = sum(x(n,j+p), p=1.. (k-1-j)) where x(n,j) = T^{(j)}(n) (mod 2). The parity sequence suffices to determine T(n,k).

A070169.name: Rounded total surface area of a regular tetrahedron with edge length n.

A070170.name: Numbers n such that sigma(n-phi(n)) = phi(n).

A070171.name: Numbers k such that sigma(phi(k)) = k-phi(k).

A070172.name: Smallest k such that sigma(k) >= n.
formula: It seems that lim n -> infinity a(n)/n*log(log(n))=C=0.6...

A070174.name: Primes p such that (p^2)! and 2^(p^2)-1 are not relatively primes.

A070175.name: The smallest representative of each (bigomega(n),omega(n)) pair.

A070176.name: Let s(n) be smallest number >= n which is a sum of two squares (A001481); sequence gives s(n) - n.

A070179.name: Primes p such that x^2 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(2^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.
formula: Primes of the form 8*k + 1 but not x^2 + 64*y^2. - _Michael Somos_, Mar 22 2008
a(n) ~ 8n log n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Nov 10 2017

A070180.name: Primes p such that x^3 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(3^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070181.name: Primes p such that x^4 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(4^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070182.name: Primes p such that x^5 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(5^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070183.name: Primes p such that x^6 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(6^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070184.name: Primes p such that x^8 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(8^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070185.name: Primes p such that x^9 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(9^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070186.name: Primes p such that x^10 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(10^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070187.name: Primes p such that x^11 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(11^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070188.name: Primes p such that x^12 = 2 has a solution mod p, but x^(12^2) = 2 has no solution mod p.

A070190.name: E.g.f.: I_0(2*x)^5 + 2*Sum_{k>=1} I_k(2*x)^5, where I_n(z) are modified Bessel functions of order n.

A070192.name: Numbers n such that n divides the numerator of B(2n) (the Bernoulli numbers), but gcd(3n,8^n+1) > 3.

A070193.name: Numbers n such that gcd(3n,8^n+1) = 3 but n does not divide the numerator of B(2n) (the Bernoulli numbers).

A070194.name: List the phi(n) numbers from 1 to n-1 which are relatively prime to n; sequence gives size of maximal gap.
formula: a(n) = max(A048669(n),2) for all n>2. Indeed A048669 is obtained when going up to n+1 instead of only n-1 (because after n+1, the gaps among numbers coprime to n repeat). Since n-1 and n+1 are both coprime to n, this means that A048669(n)=2 whenever a(n)=1, but in all other cases, there is equality. - _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 08 2012

A070195.name: Squarefree numbers in a pair of twin primes.

A070196.name: a(n)=n plus the sorted version of the base-10 digits of n.

A070197.name: Base-60 (or sexagesimal or Babylonian) expansion of sqrt(2).

A070198.name: Smallest nonnegative number m such that m == i (mod i+1) for all 1 <= i <= n.

A070199.name: Number of palindromes of length <= n.

A070200.name: Inradii of integer triangles [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)], rounded values.

A070201.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n having integral inradius.

A070202.name: Number of integer triangles with integer inradius, perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths.

A070203.name: Number of scalene integer triangles with perimeter n having integral inradius.

A070204.name: Number of isosceles integer triangles with perimeter n having integral inradius.

A070205.name: Number of acute integer triangles with perimeter n having integral inradius.

A070206.name: Number of obtuse integer triangles with perimeter n having integral inradius.

A070208.name: Number of integer triangles with perimeter n having integral area but not integral inradius.

A070209.name: Numbers n such that [A070080(n), A070081(n), A070082(n)] is an integer triangle with integer inradius.

A070211.name: Number of compositions (ordered partitions) of n that are concave-down sequences.

A070212.name: Number of 5 X 5 pandiagonal magic squares with sum n.

A070213.name: Numbers n such that a(n)=n*a(n-1)+1 with a(1)=0 is prime.

A070214.name: Maximal number of occupied cells in all monotonic matrices of order n.
formula: a(r*s) >= a(r)*a(s); if a(n) = n^e(n) then L := lim_{n->infinity} e(n) exists and is in the range 1.513 <= L <= 2.

A070215.name: Number of ways to write the n-th prime as a sum of distinct primes.

A070216.name: Triangle T(n, k) = n^2 + k^2, 1 <= k <= n, read by rows.

A070217.name: Numbers not represented by a known atomic weight as given in Francis W. Aston's Nobel lecture in 1922.

A070218.name: a(1) = 2; a(n) = smallest prime greater than the sum of all previous terms.

A070219.name: Smallest prime obtained as a concatenation of n and a number m greater than n.

A070220.name: Primes of the form n (written in base 10) followed by n 1's.

A070221.name: a(n)=LPF(n+1)-LPF(n), where LPF(n) denotes the largest prime factor of n.

A070222.name: Numbers k such that the sum of prime divisors of k divides the sum of divisors of k.

A070224.name: Numbers k such that the sum of p^2, where p are the prime divisors of k, divides the sum of d^2, where d are the divisors of k.

A070225.name: Numbers k such that (sigma(k)-k) - Sum_{p|k} p^2 = -1.
formula: a(1)=4; a(n+1) = A001359(n)^2*(A001359(n)+2) where A001359 lists number that are the lesser of twin primes.

A070226.name: Numbers n such that the squarefree kernel of n is equal to the number of divisors of n.

A070228.name: Number of perfect powers (A001597) not exceeding 2^n.
formula: a(n) = 1 - Sum_{x=2..n} Moebius(n)*floor(2^(n/x)-1). - _Robert G. Wilson v_, Jan 20 2015

A070229.name: Next m>n such that m is divisible by lpf(n), lpf=A006530 largest prime factor.
formula: a(n) = n+lpf(n) where lpf=A006530 largest prime factor. For example, a(14)=14+7=21 (instead of ((14/7)+1))*7). - Philippe Lallouet (philip.lallouet(AT)wanadoo.fr), Jun 14 2007

A070230.name: Let S_n ={p_n + q : p_n is the n-th odd prime and q runs through odd primes not greater than p_n}; sequence gives size of S_n intersect S_(n+1).

A070231.name: Let u(k), v(k), w(k) satisfy the recursions u(1) = v(1) = w(1) = 1, u(k+1) = u(k) + v(k) + w(k), v(k+1) = u(k)*v(k) + v(k)*w(k) + w(k)*u(k), and w(k+1) = u(k)*v(k)*w(k) for k >= 1; then a(n) = u(n).
formula: Let C be the positive root of x^3 + x^2 - 2*x - 1 = 0; that is, C = 1.246979603717... = A255249. Then Lim_{n -> infinity} u(n)^(C+1)/w(n)= Lim_{n -> infinity} v(n)^C/w(n) = Lim_{n -> infinity} u(n)^B/v(n) = 1 with B = C + 1 - 1/(1 + C) = 1.8019377... = A160389. [corrected by _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 11 2020]

a(n) ~ gu^((1 + C)^n), where C is defined above and gu = 1.131945853718244297... The relation between constants gu, gv (see A070234) and gw (see A070233) is gu^(1 + C) = gv^C = gw. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 11 2020

A070232.name: a(1) = 4; a(n) = smallest composite number greater than the sum of all previous terms.

A070233.name: Let u(k), v(k), w(k) satisfy the recursions u(1) = v(1) = w(1) = 1,  u(k+1) = u(k) + v(k) + w(k), v(k+1) = u(k)*v(k) + v(k)*w(k) + w(k)*u(k), and w(k+1) = u(k)*v(k)*w(k) for k >= 1; then a(n) = w(n).
formula: Let C be the positive root of x^3 + x^2 - 2*x - 1 = 0: that is, C = 1.246979603717... = A255249. Then Lim_{n  -> infinity} u(n)^(C+1)/w(n)= Lim_{n -> infinity} v(n)^C/w(n) = Lim_{n -> infinity} u(n)^B/v(n) = 1 with B = C + 1 - 1/(1 + C) = 1.8019377... = A160389. [corrected by _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 11 2020]

a(n) ~ gw^((C + 1)^n), where C is defined above and gw = 1.321128752475732548... The relation between constants gu (see A070231), gv (see A070234) and gw is gu^(1 + C) = gv^C = gw. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 11 2020

A070234.name: Let u(k), v(k), w(k) satisfy the recursions u(1) = v(1) = w(1) = 1, u(k+1) = u(k) + v(k) + w(k), v(k+1) = u(k)*v(k) + v(k)*w(k) + w(k)*u(k), and w(k+1) = u(k)*v(k)*w(k); then a(n) = v(n).
formula: Let C be the positive root of x^3 + x^2 - 2*x - 1 = 0; that is, C = 1.246979603717... = A255249. Then Lim_{n -> infinity} u(n)^(C+1)/w(n) = Lim_{n -> infinity} v(n)^C/w(n) = Lim_{n -> infinity} u(n)^B/v(n) = 1 with B = C + 1 - 1/(1 + C) = 1.8019377... = A160389. [corrected by _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 11 2020]

a(n) ~ gv^((C + 1)^n), where C is defined above and gv = 1.250231610564761084... The relation between constants gu (see A070231), gv and gw (see A070233) is gu^(1 + C) = gv^C = gw. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 11 2020

A070235.name: Number of partitions of 3^n into distinct terms.

A070236.name: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} (core(k) - phi(k)), where core(k) is the squarefree part of k.

A070237.name: Numbers n such that the sign of core(n)-phi(n) is not equal to 2*mu(n)^2-1, where core(x) is the squarefree part of x.
formula: a(n) = C*n + O(n), with C a constant conjectured to be a(2) = 420.

A070238.name: Sign of core(n)-phi(n) where core(n) is the squarefree part of n and phi the Euler totient function.

A070239.name: a(1) = 1; a(2) = 2; a(n) = sigma_a[n-2] (a[n-1]), n > 2, where sigma_k (n) denotes the sum of the k-th powers of the divisors of n.

A070243.name: a(n) = Card{ k, phi(k) <= n }.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} A014197(k); a(n) = zeta(2)*zeta(3)/zeta(6)*n + O(n*exp(-c*sqrt(log(n))) for a suitable constant c > 0. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Apr 12 2003

A070244.name: Largest palindrome using minimum number of digits with a digit sum = n.

A070245.name: Smallest palindromic prime with digit sum = n, or 0 if no such prime exists.

A070246.name: a(n) = lcm(n, R(n)) / gcd(n, R(n)), where R(n) (A004086) is the digit reversal of n.

A070251.name: Unrelated-factorial numbers: product of numbers unrelated to n (numbers which have a common divisor with n but do not divide n).

A070253.name: Numbers k such that k^2 - 1 is a palindrome.

A070254.name: Perfect squares one more than a palindrome.

A070255.name: Numbers which divided into two substrings by breaking at any digit then one of them divides the other (0 is not to be considered a substring, multiples of 10 are excluded).

A070256.name: Define P(n,X) by the recursion P(1,X)=1, P(n+1,X)=(P(n,X)+X)^2; then a(1)=0 and for n>1 a(n) is the coefficient of X^(2^(n-2)) in P(n,X) of degree 2^(n-1).

A070257.name: Fecundity of n sets a new record.

A070258.name: Smallest of 3 consecutive numbers each divisible by a square.

A070259.name: Array f(m,n) read by antidiagonals: f(m,n) = minimal number of 0's in a 2m X 2n (0,1) matrix that contains no m X n submatrix of 1's (m >= 1, n >= 1).

A070260.name: Third diagonal of triangle defined in A051537.
formula: a(n) = n*(n+2)/4 if n is even else n*(n+2).

A070261.name: 4th diagonal of triangle defined in A051537.

A070262.name: 5th diagonal of triangle defined in A051537.

A070263.name: Triangle T(n,k), n>=0, 1 <= k <= 2^n, read by rows, giving minimal distance-sum of any set of k binary vectors of length n.
formula: Rows seem to converge to expansion of 1/(1-x)^2 * sum(k>=0, 2^kt/(1-t^2), t=x^2^k). - _Ralf Stephan_, Sep 12 2003

A070264.name: Inverse permutation to that in A026098.

A070265.name: Odd powers: numbers n = m^e with e > 1 odd.
formula: a(n) ~ n^3. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Apr 20 2015

A070266.name: Maximum element in the simple continued fraction expansion of H(n)=1+1/2+1/3+...+1/n the n-th harmonic number.

A070267.name: Maximum element in the simple continued fraction expansion of e(n)=1+1/2!+1/3!+...+1/n!.

A070268.name: Numbers n such that mu(n) + mu(n+1) + mu(n+2) = -3.

A070269.name: Primes for which the smallest positive primitive root is odd and nonprime.

A070270.name: Primes for which the smallest positive primitive root is even and nonprime.

A070272.name: Numbers n such that reverse(n) = phi(n) + sigma(n).

A070273.name: Number of letters in the English names of the planets (in order from smallest orbit to largest) in 2002.

A070274.name: Numbers n such that sum of digits of n equals the squarefree part of n.

A070275.name: Numbers k such that the sum of the digits of k equals the sum of the prime divisors of k.

A070276.name: Numbers n such that sum of digits of n equals the sum of digits of n^3.

A070277.name: Smallest prime ending in n, or 0 if no such prime exists.

A070278.name: Smallest prime > 2n+1 beginning and ending with 2n+1, or 0 if no such prime exists.

A070279.name: Sum of digits of n equals the sum of digits of 2n.

A070280.name: a(1) = 1; a(n) = a(n-1) + product of the digits of n-1.

A070281.name: Smallest prime which is the sum of n consecutive primes, or 0 if no such prime exists.

A070282.name: a(1) = 1; a(2) = 2; a(n) = [sum of digits of a(n-1)]^[sum of digits of a(n-2)] for n > 2.

A070283.name: a(1) = 1; a(2) = 2; a(n) = [product of digits of a(n-1)]^[product of digits of a(n-2)] for n > 2.

A070284.name: Smallest of 4 consecutive numbers each divisible by a square.

A070286.name: Numbers n such that the equation sigma(sigma(x)) = n has solutions.

A070287.name: Numbers n such that the equation lcm(sigma(x),phi(x))=n has solutions.

A070288.name: a(n) = Sum_{d|n} omega(d)*omega(n/d).
formula: a(n) = Sum_{prime p|n} A062799(n/p) = Sum_{prime p|n} Sum_{prime q|(n/p)} A000005(n/p/q). - _Max Alekseyev_, Aug 11 2016

A070289.name: Number of distinct values of multinomial coefficients ( n / (p1, p2, p3, ...) ) where (p1, p2, p3, ...) runs over all partitions of n.

A070294.name: Smallest k such that k==i (mod(i!+1)) i=1,2,3,...,n.

A070295.name: Smallest composite number such that there are exactly n primes less than it (and coprime to it) which do not divide it, or 0 if no such number exists.

A070296.name: Let sphi(k) = number of primes less than k and coprime to it (A048865); then a(n) = number of integers m with sphi(m) = n.
formula: a(n) = number of m such that A048865(m) = n.

A070297.name: Smallest number with n unrelated numbers (numbers which are neither coprime nor a divisor), or 0 if no such number exists.

A070298.name: Let Unrel(m) = number of unrelated numbers less than m; then a(n) = number of values of m for which Unrel(m) = n.

A070299.name: Numbers n such that sigma(n+x) = sigma(n-x) for some 0 < x < n.

A070300.name: Minimal number of 0's in a 2n X 2n (0,1) matrix that contains no n X n submatrix of 1's.

A070301.name: Numbers n such that sum of first 2n primes is prime.

A070302.name: Number of 3 X 3 X 3 magic cubes with sum 3n.
formula: G.f.: x*(x^4 + 14x^3 + 36x^2 + 14x + 1)/(1 - x)^5. [corrected by _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 26 2010]
Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n) = 2*Pi*(sqrt(17 + 4*sqrt(5)) * tanh(sqrt(17/44 - sqrt(5)/11)*Pi) - sqrt(17 - 4*sqrt(5))*tanh(sqrt(17/44 + sqrt(5)/11)*Pi)) / sqrt(95). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 01 2018

A070303.name: Primes p such that the equation p^2*x^2==0 (mod p^2+x^2) has no solution.
formula: Primes not in A002496 (i.e., not of the form k^2+1).
a(n) ~ n log n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 30 2012

A070304.name: a(n) = number of times n^2*k^2/(n^2+k^2) is an integer as k ranges over 0, 1, 2, ...

A070305.name: Numbers n such that Card(k>0 : phi(k)=phi(n)) = tau(n).
formula: Numbers k such that A066412(k) = A000005(k).

A070307.name: Number of n X n matrices with nonnegative integer entries such that every row sum equals 3.

A070308.name: "Canada perfect numbers": n such that the sum of digits^2 of n equals the sum of d|n, 1<d<n.

A070309.name: Number of solutions 2<=x<=A060679(n) to the equation x^A060679(n)==1 (mod A060679(n)) where A060679(n) are the orders of non-cyclic groups.

A070310.name: Numbers n such that the sum of its aliquot parts and the number of its divisors are both perfect numbers.

A070311.name: Numbers n such that sopfr(n) and d(n) are both perfect numbers.

A070312.name: a(1) = a(2) = 1; a(n) = a(n-1) + concatenation of a(n-2) and a(n-1).

A070314.name: P(n!+1)-P(2^n+1) where P(x) is the largest prime factor in x.

A070315.name: Third diagonal of triangle in A046739.

A070316.name: Numbers n such that nextprime(n^2)-n^2 (n>=1) sets a new record.

A070317.name: Record values of nextprime(n^2)-n^2, cf. A070316.

A070318.name: Max( sigma(k)-k : k=1,2,3,...,n ) where sigma(x)-x is the sum of proper divisors of x.

A070319.name: Max( tau(k) : k=1,2,3,...,n ) where tau(n)=A000005(n) is the number of divisors of x.
formula: a(n) = exp(log(2) log(n) / log(log(n)) + O(log(n) log(log(log(n))) / (log(log(n)))^2)). (See Sándor reference for more formulas.) - _Eric M. Schmidt_, Jun 30 2013

A070322.name: Number of primitive n X n real (0,1)-matrices.
formula: For asymptotics see Sachkov and Tarakanov.

A070323.name: Let M_n be the n X n matrix m(i,j)=min(prime(i), prime(j)); then a(n)=det(M_n).

A070325.name: Numbers n such that n+1, n^2+1 and n^4+1 are primes.

A070326.name: Upper triangular array giving for each (x,y) the minimum modulus m such that x^3+y^3 is not congruent to a cube (mod m).

A070327.name: Smallest nontrivial power of n starting with n and greater than n.
formula: f[n_] := Block[{k = 2, s = ToString[n]}, While[ StringPosition[ ToString[n^k], s, 1] != {{1, Integer_}}, k++ ]; n^k]; Table[ f[n], {n, 2, 10}]

A070328.name: Numbers in which inserting, prefixing or suffixing a 1 anywhere yields only composite numbers.

A070329.name: Nontrivial numbers in which inserting, prefixing or suffixing a 1 anywhere yields only composite numbers.

A070330.name: Nontrivial numbers in which suffixing or inserting a 0 anywhere yields only composite numbers.

A070331.name: Numbers in which suffixing or inserting a 0 anywhere yields only composite numbers.

A070332.name: Smallest nontrivial power of n ending in n and greater than n; or 0 if no such number exists.

A070352.name: a(n) = 3^n mod 5; or period 4, repeat [1, 3, 4, 2].
formula: a(n) = a(n-4) for n>3. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jul 09 2016

A070376.name: a(n) = 5^n mod 26.
formula: a(n) = 13 - 2*((3+2*i)*(-i)^n + (3-2*i)*i^n), where i = sqrt(-1). - _Bruno Berselli_, Feb 07 2011

A070403.name: a(n) = 7^n mod 9.
formula: a(n) = a(n-3) for n>3. - _G. C. Greubel_, Mar 19 2016

A070418.name: Numbers n such that n and phi(n) have the same number of divisors.

A070428.name: Number of perfect powers (A001597) not exceeding 10^n.

A070432.name: Period 4: repeat [0, 1, 4, 1]; a(n) = n^2 mod 8.
formula: Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s)*(1 + 4*2^(-s))*(1 - 2^(-s)). - _R. J. Mathar_, Mar 10 2011
a(n) = a(-n) for all n in Z. - _Michael Somos_, Dec 22 2016

A070435.name: a(n) = n^2 mod 12, or alternately n^4 mod 12.

A070447.name: a(n) = n^2 mod 25.
formula: a(n) = (n + 25h); a(n) = 0 if n == 0 (mod 5). Also, a(r) = a(s) if r+s == 0 (mod 25). - _Vincenzo Librandi_, Dec 18 2014

A070486.name: a(n) = n^3 mod 24 (or equivalently, n^5 mod 24).

A070502.name: a(n) = n^3 mod 40.
formula: a(n+40) = a(n). If n even, a(n+20) = a(n). - _R. J. Mathar_, Sep 25 2008

A070514.name: Final digit of n^4: n^4 mod 10.
formula: a(n) = n^k mod 10; for k > 0 where k mod 4 = 0. - _Doug Bell_, Jun 15 2015

A070518.name: Value of n-th cyclotomic polynomial at n.

A070519.name: Numbers k such that Cyclotomic(k,k) (i.e., the value of k-th cyclotomic polynomial at k) is a prime number.

A070521.name: Value of prime(n)-th cyclotomic polynomial at n.

A070522.name: Value of n-th cyclotomic polynomial at the n-th prime.

A070523.name: Numbers k such that cyclotomic(k, prime(k)) is a prime number.

A070524.name: Value of n-th cyclotomic polynomial at phi(n).

A070525.name: Numbers n such that n-th cyclotomic polynomial evaluated at phi(n) is a prime number.

A070526.name: Value of n-th cyclotomic polynomial at 2^n.

A070527.name: Numbers k such that cyclotomic(k, 2^k) is a prime number.

A070528.name: Number of divisors of 10^n-1 (999...999 with n digits).

A070529.name: Number of divisors of repunit 111...111 (with n digits).

A070531.name: Generalized Bell numbers B_{4,3}.
formula: a(n)=sum(A090440(n, k), k=3..3*n)= sum((1/k!)*product(fallfac(k+(j-1)*(4-3), 3), j=1..n), k=3..infinity)/exp(1), n>=1. From eq.(9) of the Blasiak et al. reference with r=4, s=3. fallfac(n, m) := A008279(n, m) (falling factorials triangle). a(0) := 1 may be added.

A070536.name: Number of terms in n-th cyclotomic polynomial minus largest prime factor of n; a(1)=1 by convention.

A070537.name: Numbers such that the n-th cyclotomic polynomial has more terms than the largest prime factor of n.
formula: Numbers n satisfying A070536(n) = A051664(n) - A006530(n) > 0.

A070542.name: Numbers n such that binomial(2n,n) does not have two prime factors that add to 2n.

A070543.name: Triangular array read by rows: T(n,k) = number of k-dimensional isotropic subspaces of Spin(2n+1,C), n >= 1, 1 <= k <= n.

By induction, a(1)=a(2)=1, a(3)=a(4)=a(5)=3 and for k >= 3 we obtain the following formulas for the 2k-1 consecutive values from a(k^2-2k+2) up to a(k^2+1): a(k^2+1) = a(k^2) = 2k-1, if 1 <= i <= 2k-3 then a(k^2-i) = 2k-2-(-1)^i, hence asymptotically a(n) ~ 2*sqrt(n). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Jul 28 2002

A070882.name: Least k such that A070867(k) = n, or 0 if no such k exist.

A070883.name: Bitwise XOR of n and n-th prime.
formula: a(n) = 2*OR(p,n) - (p+n), for n-th prime p. - _Gary Detlefs_, Oct 26 2013

A070884.name: 7 + x where x is congruent to {0, 4, 6, 10, 12, 16, 22, 24} mod 30.

A070885.name: a(n) = (3/2)*a(n-1) if a(n-1) is even; (3/2)*(a(n-1)+1) if a(n-1) is odd.
formula: For n > 1, a(n) = 3*A061419(n) = 3*floor(K*(3/2)^n) where K=1.08151366859... - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 18 2002
a(n+1) = a(n) + A081848(n), for n > 1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 05 2014

A070886.name: Triangle read by rows giving successive states of cellular automaton generated by "Rule 90".

A070887.name: Triangle read by rows giving successive states of one-dimensional cellular automaton generated by "Rule 110".

A070890.name: Numerator of Sum_{k=1..n} mu(k)/k when it changes sign.

A070891.name: Denominator of Sum_{k=1..n} mu(k)/k when it changes sign.

A070892.name: Numbers n such that absolute value of Sum_{k=1..n} mu(k)/k sets a new minimum.

A070893.name: Let r, s, t be three permutations of the set {1,2,3,..,n}; a(n) = value of Sum_{i=1..n} r(i)*s(i)*t(i), with r={1,2,3,..,n}; s={n,n-1,..,1} and t={n,n-2,n-4,...,1,...,n-3,n-1}.
formula: a(n) = 3*a(n-1) - 2*a(n-2) - 2*a(n-3) + 3*a(n-4) - a(n-5) + 3. If sequence is also defined for n <= 0 by this equation, then a(n)=0 for -3 <= n <= 0 and a(n)=A082289(-n) for n <= -4. - _Michael Somos_, Apr 07 2003

A070894.name: Number of nonempty subsets of the set of vertices of a regular n-gon in the plane such that their center of gravity is the center of the polygon.

A070895.name: Triangle read by rows where T(n+1,k)=T(n,k)+n*T(n-1,k) starting with T(n,n)=1 and T(n,k)=0 if n<k.

A070896.name: Determinant of the Cayley addition table of Z_{n}.

A070897.name: Number of ways of pairing numbers 1 to n with numbers n+1 to 2n such that each pair sums to a prime.
formula: a(n) = permanent(m), where the n X n matrix m is defined by m(i,j) = 1 or 0, depending on whether i+j+n is prime or composite, respectively. - _T. D. Noe_, Feb 10 2007

A070898.name: a(0)=1, a(n) is the smallest integer > a(n-1) such that the largest element in the simple continued fraction for S(n)= 1/a(0)+1/a(1)+1/a(2)+...+1/a(n) equals 2n.

A070899.name: a(1)=1, a(n) is the smallest integer > a(n-1) such that the largest element in the simple continued fraction for S(n)=1/a(1)+1/a(2)+...+1/a(n) equals 3n.

A070900.name: a(0)=1, a(n) is the smallest integer > a(n-1) such that the largest element in the simple continued fraction for S(n)=1/a(0)+1/a(1)+1/a(2)+...+1/a(n) equals the number of elements in this continued fraction.

A070901.name: a(1)=1, a(n) is the smallest integer > a(n-1) such that the largest element in the simple continued fraction for S(n)=1/a(1)+1/a(2)+...+1/a(n) equals prime(n).

A070902.name: a(1)=1, a(n) is the smallest integer > a(n-1) such that the largest element in the simple continued fraction for S(n)=1/a(1)+1/a(2)+...+1/a(n) equals n^2.

A070903.name: a(1)=1, a(n) is the smallest integer > a(n-1) such that the largest element in the simple continued fraction for S(n)=1/a(1)+1/a(2)+...+1/a(n) equals n^3.

A070904.name: a(1) = 1, a(n) is the smallest integer > a(n-1) such that the largest element in the simple continued fraction for S(n) = 1/a(1) + 1/a(2) + ... + 1/a(n) equals n^4.

A070905.name: Smallest prime (emirp) of n consecutive primes such that all are emirps and all have the same digital sum.

A070906.name: Every third Bell number A000110.
formula: E.g.f.: exp(x*(d_z)^3)*(exp(exp(z)-1)) |_{z=0}, with the derivative operator d_z := d/dz. Adapted from eqs. (14) and (15) of the 1999 C. M. Bender reference given in A000110.

A070907.name: Every fourth Bell number A000110.
formula: E.g.f.: exp(x*(d_z)^4)*(exp(exp(z)-1)) |_{z=0}, with the derivative operator d_z := d/dz. Adapted from eqs. (14) and (15) of the 1999 C. M. Bender reference given in A000110.

A070908.name: Every fifth Bell number A000110.
formula: E.g.f.: exp(x*(d_z)^5)*(exp(exp(z)-1)) |_{z=0}, with the derivative operator d_z := d/dz. Adapted from eqs. (14) and (15) of the 1999 C. M. Bender reference given in A000110.

A070909.name: Triangle read by rows giving successive states of cellular automaton generated by "Rule 28" and by "Rule 156".

A070910.name: Decimal expansion of BesselI(0,2).
formula: This continued fraction is the particular case k = 0 of the result BesselI(k,2) = sum {n = 0..inf} 1/(n!*(n+k)!) = 1/(k! - k!/((k+2) -(k+1)/((2*k+5) - 2*(k+2)/((3*k+10) - ... - n*(n+k)/(((n+1)*(n+k+1)+1) - ...))))). See the remarks in A099597 for a sketch of the proof. (End)

A070911.name: a(n) is twice the least possible area enclosed by a convex lattice n-gon.

A070914.name: Array read by antidiagonals giving number of paths up and left from (0,0) to (n,kn) where x/y <= k for all intermediate points.
formula: If P(k,x) = Sum_{n>=0} T(n,k)*x^n is the g.f. of column k (k>=0), then P(k,x) = exp(1/(k+1)*(Sum_{j>0} 1/j*binomial((k+1)*j,j)*x^j)). - _Werner Schulte_, Oct 13 2015

A070915.name: Numbers having at most two distinct prime factors.
formula: a(n) ~ n log n/log log n. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Oct 16 2015

A070916.name: a(1)=1, a(n) is the smallest integer => a(n-1) such that a(n)a(n-1)-1 is prime.
formula: Conjecture : lim n -> infinity a(n)/n/Log(n) = C = 1.075...

A070917.name: Numbers n such that the number of steps to reach 1 in the "3x+1" (or Collatz) problem divides n.

A070918.name: Triangle of T(n,k) coefficients of polynomials with first n prime numbers as roots.

A070919.name: a(n) = Card{ (x,y,z) | lcm(x,y,z)=n }.
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = 1+3*e+3*e^2 for prime p and e >= 0. - _Werner Schulte_, Nov 30 2018

A070922.name: First palindromic prime pyramids with a(1)=2 such that (number of digits in a(n+1)) = (number of digits in a(n)) + 2.

A070923.name: a(n) is the smallest value >= 0 of the form x^3 - n^2.

A070924.name: Where A070871 sets a new record.

A070925.name: Number of subsets of A = {1,2,...,n} that have the same center of gravity as A, i.e., (n+1)/2.

A070926.name: Records in the Conway's alimentary function A070871.

A070927.name: Second palindromic prime pyramids with a(1)=2 such that (number of digits in a(n+1)) = (number of digits in a(n)) + 2.

A070928.name: Smallest integer >= 0 of the form x^4 - n^3.

A070929.name: Smallest integer >= 0 of the form x^2 - n^3.

A070930.name: Smallest integer >= 0 of the form x^3 - n^4.

A070931.name: Numbers k such that the smallest integer value >= 0 of the form x^3 - k^2 equals the smallest integer value >= 0 of the form x^2 - k^3.
formula: Numbers k such that ceiling(k^(2/3))^3 - k^2 = ceiling(k^(3/2))^2 - k^3.

A070932.name: Possible number of units in a (commutative or non-commutative) ring.

A070933.name: Expansion of Product_{k>=1} 1/(1 - 2*t^k).
formula: Euler transform of A000031(n). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Jun 23 2004
a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} p(n,k)*A000079(k) where p(n,k) = number of integer partitions of n into k parts. - _Thomas Wieder_, May 07 2008
a(n) = S(n,1), where S(n,m) = 2 + Sum_{k=m..floor(n/2)} 2*S(n-k,k)), S(n,n)=2, S(0,m)=1, S(n,m)=0 for n < m. - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Sep 07 2014

a(n) = Sum_{lambda,mu,nu} (c^{lambda}_{mu,nu})^2, where lambda ranges over all partitions of n, mu and nu range over all partitions satisfying |mu| + |nu| = n, and c^{lambda}_{mu,nu} denotes a Littlewood-Richardson coefficient. - _Richard Stanley_, Nov 16 2014
G.f.: Product_{j>=1} Product_{i>=1} 1/(1-x^(i*j))^A001037(j) given in Morrison link section 2.9. - _Geoffrey Critzer_, May 26 2021

A070934.name: Smallest prime equal to the sum of 2n+1 consecutive primes.

A070936.name: Square array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) = number of partitions of n into distinct parts, each no more than k.

A070937.name: Number of times maximal coefficient (A025591) appears in Product_{k<=n} (x^k + 1), i.e., number of times highest value appears in n-th row of A053632 or n-th column of A070936.
formula: If n mod 4 = 0 or 3 then a(n) odd, otherwise a(n) even.

A070938.name: Harshad numbers which terminate in their digital sum.

A070939.name: Length of binary representation of n.
formula: a(0)=1, a(1)=1 and a(n) = 1+a(floor(n/2)). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Dec 02 2003
a(2^m + k) = m + 1, m >= 0, 0 <= k < 2^m. - _Yosu Yurramendi_, Mar 14 2017

A070940.name: Number of digits that must be counted from left to right to reach the last 1 in the binary representation of n.
formula: a(n) = f(n, 1), f(n, k) = if n=1 then k else f(floor(n/2), k+(if k>1 then 1 else n mod 2)). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Feb 01 2003
G.f.: sum(k>=0, t/(1-t^2) * [1 + sum(l>=1, t^2^l)], t=x^2^k). - _Ralf Stephan_, Mar 15 2004

A070941.name: Length of binary representation of 2n+1.
formula: Let b(1)=1, b(n) = a(n-floor(n/2)) + 1, then a(n) = b(n+1). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Oct 23 2002
a(n) = ceiling(average of previous entries) + 1. - _Jon Perry_, Apr 04 2004

A070942.name: Values of n such that the first n terms of A055265 constitute a permutation of {1,2,3,...,n}.

A070943.name: Commuting elements: number of ordered pairs g, h in the group GL(2,Z_n) such that gh = hg.
formula: a(n) = A000252(n) * A062354(n) = n^4 * product (1-1/p^2)*(1-1/p) * sigma(n)*phi(n) ( where the product is over all the primes p that divide n ).

A070945.name: Number of permutations on n letters that have only cycles of length 4 or less.

A070946.name: Number of permutations on n letters that have only cycles of length 5 or less.

A070947.name: Number of permutations on n letters that have only cycles of length 6 or less.

A070948.name: a(0) = 1; a(n+1) = smallest number > a(n) such that a(0)*a(1)*...*a(n) + 1 is a square.

A070950.name: Triangle read by rows giving successive states of cellular automaton generated by "Rule 30".
formula: The following recurrence expresses the rules in rule 30, except that instead of If, Or, And, Not, we use addition, subtraction, and multiplication.
Discarding the term after the plus sign, multiplying/expanding the terms out and replacing all exponents with ones, gives us this simplified recurrence:

A070951.name: Number of 0's in n-th row of triangle in A070950.

A070952.name: Number of 1's in n-th generation of 1-D CA using Rule 30, started with a single 1.

A070953.name: Order of the group GU(n,2), the general unitary n X n matrices over the finite field GF(4).

A070954.name: Emirps which when concatenated with their reversals after a 0 make a palindromic prime of the form emirp0prime.

A070955.name: Numbers n such that n concatenated with n-1 0's and its reversal is prime.

A070956.name: Number of pairs (x,y) such that n = gcd(x,y) + lcm(x,y).

A070957.name: Primes p such that the equation sigma(x)=p has no solution.

A070958.name: Numbers n such that the largest digit of n is the same as the largest digit of (sum of digits of n).

A070959.name: First minimum value > 0 of the form x^3-k^2 when k > n^3.
formula: Let k be the smallest integer>n^3 such that A070923(k-1)> A070923(k) and such that A070923(k) < A070923(k+1), then a(n)= A070923(k); for n>=1 a(2n-1) = 8n^3-9n^2+6n-1, a(2n)=3n^2+1.

A070962.name: Card{ k<=n | omega(k)!=omega(n) }, where omega(n) = A001221(n).
formula: lim a(n)/n = 1. This follows from the Erdos-Kac theorem on the distribution of values of omega(n) - see the Weisstein link. - _Dean Hickerson_, Jan 29 2006

A070963.name: a(1) = 2; for n >= 2, n = Sum_{1<=k<n, gcd(k,n)=1} a(k).

A070965.name: a(1) = 1; a(n+1) = sum{k|n} a(k) * mu(k), where the sum is over the positive divisors, k, of n; and mu(k) is the Moebius function.

A070966.name: a(n) = Sum_{k|n, k<=sqrt(n)} phi(k); where the sum is over the positive divisors, k, of n, which are <= the square root of n; and phi(k) is the Euler totient function.

A070967.name: a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(6*n,6*k).
formula: Let b(n)=a(n)-2^(6n)/6 then b(n)+26*b(n-1)-27*b(n-2)=0 - _Benoit Cloitre_, May 27 2004

A070968.name: Number of cycles in the complete bipartite graph K(n,n).

A070970.name: Smallest number k such that A065422(k)/A065422(k+1) = k^n, where k>1.

A070971.name: a(n) is the smallest positive integer m for which A070194(m) (i.e., the maximal gap in {k|gcd(k,m) = 1, 1 <= k <= m-1}) is n.

A070972.name: Length of longest run of consecutive 1's in binary expansion of 3^n (A004656).

A070973.name: Smallest integer k such that n divides floor((3/2)^k).

A070974.name: Number of steps to reach 1 in `3x+1' (or Collatz) problem starting with n!.

A070975.name: Number of steps to reach 1 in `3x+1' (or Collatz) problem starting with prime(n).

A070976.name: Number of steps to reach 1 in '3x+1' (or Collatz) problem starting with 3^n.

A070977.name: Smallest k such that zeta(3)-sum(i=1,k,1/i^3) <= zeta(4)-sum(i=1,n,1/i^4).

A070978.name: Smallest k such that zeta(4)-sum(i=1,k,1/i^4) <= zeta(5)-sum(i=1,n,1/i^5).

A070979.name: Triangle read by rows giving size of minimal asymmetric covering code of length n and radius R.

A070980.name: Numbers k such that the number of steps to reach 1 in '3x+1' problem equals tau(k), the number of divisors of k.

A070981.name: Smallest integer k such that n divides floor((4/3)^k).

A070982.name: Smallest integer k such that n divides sigma(k).
formula: Sum(k=1, n, a(k)) seems to be asymptotic to c*n^2 with probably 1.1 < c < 1.2.
By Xylouris' form of Linnk's theorem, a(n) << n^5. Can this be improved? - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Mar 09 2017

A070985.name: Number of terms in simple continued fraction for sum(k=1,n,1/k^2).

A070986.name: Number of terms in simple continued fraction for sum(k=1,n,1/k^3).

A070987.name: Number of terms in simple continued fraction for sum(k=1,n,1/k^4).

A070991.name: Numbers n such that the trajectory of n under the `3x+1' map reaches n - 1.

A070993.name: Numbers n such that the trajectory of n under the "3x+1" map reaches n+1.

A070994.name: Numbers n such that the trajectory of n under the `3x+1' map reaches phi(n).

A070995.name: Number of nonisomorphic (undirected) Cayley graphs for the group Zp x Zp, where Zp is the elementary Abelian group of order p and p is prime. The sequence is index by primes, though starts with 1.

A070996.name: Numbers n whose sum of divisors and number of divisors are both triangular numbers.

A070997.name: a(n) = 8*a(n-1) - a(n-2), a(0)=1, a(-1)=1.
formula: For all members x of the sequence, 15*x^2 - 6 is a square. Lim_{n->infinity} a(n)/a(n-1) = 4 + sqrt(15). - _Gregory V. Richardson_, Oct 12 2002
a(n) = U(n, 4)-U(n-1, 4) = T(2*n+1, sqrt(5/2))/sqrt(5/2), with Chebyshev's U and T polynomials and U(-1, x) := 0. U(n, 4)=A001090(n+1), n>=-1.
Let q(n, x) = Sum_{i=0..n} x^(n-i)*binomial(2*n-i, i); then q(n, 6) = a(n) - _Benoit Cloitre_, Nov 10 2002
a(n) = (-1)^n*U(2n, i*sqrt(6)/2), U(n, x) Chebyshev polynomial of second kind, i=sqrt(-1). - _Paul Barry_, Mar 13 2005
For n>0, a(n) is the numerator of the continued fraction [2,3,2,3,...,2,3] with n repetitions of 2,3. For the denominators see A136325. - _Greg Dresden_, Sep 12 2019

A070998.name: a(n) = 9*a(n-1) - a(n-2) for n > 0, a(0)=1, a(-1)=1.
formula: Let q(n, x) = Sum_{i=0..n} x^(n-i)*binomial(2*n-i, i); then q(n, 7) = a(n). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Nov 10 2002
a(n) = (-1)^n*U(2n, i*sqrt(7)/2), U(n, x) Chebyshev polynomial of second kind, i=sqrt(-1). - _Paul Barry_, Mar 13 2005

A070999.name: Numbers n such that the denominator of Sum_{k=1..n} 1/gcd(n,k) is not equal to n.

A071000.name: Numbers n such that the denominator of Sum_{k=1..n} 1/gcd(n,k) equals n.
